'''Bead Town''' is a [[Travelling exhibition|traveling]] art [[Art exhibition|exhibit]] of 100 huge [[mosaics]] composed of [[recycle]]d [[Mardi Gras]] beads. Created by [[carpenter]] and artist [[Stephan Wanger]] in [[New Orleans]], [[Louisiana]], Bead Town has been exhibited in [[Winnsboro, Louisiana]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thenewsstar.com/article/20120906/LIFESTYLE/209060307/-Bead-Town-exhibit-opens-Winnsboro/ |title=Accent - The News Star - thenewsstar.com |work=[[The News-Star]] |date=September 6, 2012 |accessdate=7 August 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150723041312/http://www.thenewsstar.com/article/20120906/LIFESTYLE/209060307/-Bead-Town-exhibit-opens-Winnsboro |archivedate=23 July 2015 |df= }}</ref> [[Natchitoches, Louisiana]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ktbs.com/story/22658387/bead-town-art-exhibit-open-in-natchitoches|title=Bead Town art exhibit open in Natchitoches|date=21 June 2013|work=[[KTBS-TV|KTBS]]|accessdate=7 August 2015}}</ref> and [[Gary, Indiana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nwitimes.com/news/local/lake/gary/mardi-gras-mosaics-bead-town-opens-in-gary/article_420f1b59-6aaf-5924-81c9-51d3c88ad2fb.html|title=Mardi Gras mosaics: Bead Town opens in Gary|author=Rob Earnshaw Times Correspondent|work=[[The Times of Northwest Indiana]]|date=January 9, 2014|accessdate=7 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nwitimes.com/news/local/lake/merrillville/gary-students-become-part-of-bead-art-culture/article_58c7e4b0-ba3c-59c8-8d38-a042ee33798f.html|title=Gary students become part of bead art culture|work=[[The Times of Northwest Indiana]]|date=June 24, 2015|accessdate=8 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lsureveille.com/daily/mardi-gras-bead-art-dazzles-the-community/article_13f205de-b0bb-11e4-95eb-cb975deac34e.html|title=Mardi Gras bead art dazzles the community|work=[[The Daily Reveille]]|date=February 9, 2015|accessdate=8 August 2015}}</ref>

